al. Heid. gr. 23. De Stefani in his edition of Silentiary's text pointed out several imitations of Silentiary by Constantine. Further imitations of Silentiary's poem came out in course of the elaboration of this project and are recorded in the fontes. Constantine's poem is wordly "ed by Georgius Cedrenus. This new very important tool would help to better both the text we are editing and the "ations by Cedrenus listed in the fontes. Finally, the apparatus of the fontes will also mention the most patent imitations of the poem of Constantine by later Byzantine poets. The book will be a useful tool for all students of Byzantine literature.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aChristentum. 4aConstantinus‹Rhodius›. 4aLiteratur (Byzanz). 4aPaphlago, Theodorus. 4aSpätantike. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aByzantine History.  aByzantine Literature.  aByzantium.  aGreek philology.1 aDe Stefani, Claudio, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStrano, Gioacchino, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTheodorus Paphlago, , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023z9783111318110oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311074215240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074246640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110742466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110742466/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-